    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-and-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-and-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-and-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fresh</strong> <strong>tagliatelle</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tagliatelle</strong> for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> tagliatelle</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-and-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>,<strong> dried oregano </strong>and<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong> with 80ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [100ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [130ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-and-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper has softened, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until the sauce thickens slightly</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-and-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained tagliatelle </strong>to the sauce with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>sweet</strong> <strong>pepper & tomato tagliatelle</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-and-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sweet</strong> <strong>pepper & tomato tagliatelle </strong>topped with your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped basil </strong>and a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
